OL,3,CNI sex anonymity law appeal 'always an
OL,4,Coption,' says Long
OL,6,F"This was on the basis that the
OL,7,Fprovision criminalised publication of
OL,8,Fa suspect's details without
OL,9,Frecognising any public interest
OL,10,Fdefence and failed to provide for a
OL,11,Fprocess by which media organisations
OL,12,Fmay apply to the court during a
OL,13,Fsuspect's lifetime to have the
OL,14,Fprohibition on publication modified or
OL,15,Frevoked on public interest grounds.
OL,17,F"The other grounds of challenge, which
OL,18,Frelated to the retrospective effect of
OL,19,Fthe provision and an alleged lack of
OL,20,Fprocedural fairness, were not upheld.
